To subtract these two numbers, we first need to borrow from the left. 

Then, 
\[ \begin{array}{}
& & & 3 & 7 & 5 & 6 & 2_{9}\\ 
& - & 4 & 1 & 7 & 2 & 4_{9}\\ 
\end{array} \]

We borrow from the left to get:
\[ \begin{array}{}
& & & 2_{9} & 16 & 15 & 16 & 2_{9}\\ 
& - & 4 & 1 & 7 & 2 & 4_{9}\\ 
& & & & 3 & 8 & 13_{9}\\ 
\end{array} \]

Then, we continue to borrow until the second column: 
\[ \begin{array}{}
& & & 1 & 15 & 14_{9} & 16 & 2_{9}\\ 
& - & 4 & 1 & 7 & 2 & 4_{9}\\ 
& & & & 8 & 6 & 16_{9}\\ 
\end{array} \]

Then, we continue to borrow until the third column: 
\[ \begin{array}{}
& & & 0 & 24_{9} & 14_{9} & 16 & 2_{9}\\ 
& - & 4 & 1 & 7 & 2 & 4_{9}\\ 
& & & 8 & 15_{9} & 14_{9} & 16_{9}\\ 
\end{array} \]

Finally, we get 
\[ 37562_{9} - 41724_{9} = 81516_{9} \]

Therefore, 
\[ 37562_{9} - 41724_{9} = 81516_{9} \]